Make rumpel list use cached pod state by default

`rumpel list` no longer probes container backends unless the user asks
for a synchronized view.  The default output uses the daemon's pod
connection state, which is already maintained by each pod's event
stream.

Add `rumpel list --sync` for callers that need a live refresh before
printing, including an explicit pod ref push so host-side git state is
up to date before list computes ahead/behind status.
